00:27:28,746 --> 00:27:33,660
We're watching Senator Palmer work the
room a little bit before he gets to the speech...

232
00:27:40,304 --> 00:27:42,499
Milo, come here.

233
00:27:43,304 --> 00:27:45,453
- You were right.
- About what?

234
00:27:46,183 --> 00:27:48,901
The key card. It was a forgery.
We found the original.

235
00:27:48,982 --> 00:27:51,290
- Where?
- Jack's office.

236
00:27:51,382 --> 00:27:53,575
- Why did he swap it out?
- Doesn't matter.

237
00:27:53,662 --> 00:27:56,891
Look, I sent it down to Archiving
to make a backup of all the data.

238
00:27:56,980 --> 00:28:00,131
Then it's going straight to you.
You'll have to work quickly.

239
00:28:00,219 --> 00:28:02,210
Just get it to me.

240
00:28:04,898 --> 00:28:07,617
A forged key card. What's that about?

241
00:28:08,338 --> 00:28:10,055
I have no idea.

242
00:28:21,534 --> 00:28:23,650
She's squirming.

243
00:28:27,692 --> 00:28:30,649
- Almeida.
- This is Pierce from Secret Service.

244
00:28:30,731 --> 00:28:34,519
Aaron, I called you because we have
new information you should know about.

245
00:28:34,730 --> 00:28:38,961
- One of our agents, Jack Bauer, may be there.
- Yeah, he's here. I cleared him.

246
00:28:39,049 --> 00:28:42,404
Well, we learned that
he may have been compromised.

247
00:28:43,008 --> 00:28:46,795
- He may not be acting to protect the senator.
- Are you saying he's a threat?

248
00:28:48,846 --> 00:28:50,278
Yeah.

249
00:28:50,366 --> 00:28:52,720
Take the appropriate actions.

250
00:28:52,805 --> 00:28:54,796
She's on the move.

251
00:29:06,602 --> 00:29:09,478
OK, ladies' rest room. Second-to-last stall.

252
00:29:09,561 --> 00:29:12,233
- These cameras are on a 20-second loop.
- Am I clear?

253
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,556
No, not yet.

254
00:29:28,437 --> 00:29:29,835
Go. You got 20 seconds.

255
00:29:38,273 --> 00:29:40,150
Get out. Now.

256
00:29:40,232 --> 00:29:41,824
Get out!

257
00:29:44,071 --> 00:29:46,504
Get out! Out! Go!

258
00:29:57,948 --> 00:30:03,226
I gotta keep you guys working. The fatter
your pay cheque, the more tax you can afford.

259
00:30:05,587 --> 00:30:07,894
Excuse me, guys.

260
00:30:07,986 --> 00:30:10,738
- What's up?
- I just got a call from CTU.

261
00:30:10,824 --> 00:30:13,054
- We need to get you out of here, sir.
- Why?

262
00:30:13,304 --> 00:30:16,898
- There's a problem with one of their agents.
- What kind of problem?

263
00:30:16,982 --> 00:30:19,656
He could be a threat to you.

264
00:30:19,742 --> 00:30:22,858
If he's one of ours, find him
and take care of this quietly.

265
00:30:22,941 --> 00:30:25,011
We are trying, sir.

266
00:30:26,901 --> 00:30:30,575
I tell you what. I'll lose the
face time, but the speech stays.

267
00:30:30,659 --> 00:30:34,971
- There's something I have to say.
- With all due respect, it's a mistake, sir.

268
00:30:35,058 --> 00:30:39,050
This information comes
directly from CTU headquarters.

269
00:30:40,216 --> 00:30:43,049
I am sure your people will take care of us.

270
00:30:51,133 --> 00:30:54,330
All right, everyone on the floor,
listen up. This is Pierce.

271
00:30:54,414 --> 00:30:59,122
Palmer has decided to proceed.
I repeat, Palmer will remain.

272
00:30:59,212 --> 00:31:02,044
We need to locate and detain a suspect.

273
00:31:02,131 --> 00:31:04,406
His name is Jack Bauer.

274
00:31:04,650 --> 00:31:08,768
Bauer's 5'11", blond hair, 160 pounds.

275
00:31:08,849 --> 00:31:10,726
He is wearing a dark...

276
00:31:10,809 --> 00:31:14,118
brown jacket that may display CTU ID.

277
00:31:14,208 --> 00:31:17,643
This is Hayes. Possible 20 on Bauer.
How would you like me to proceed?

278
00:31:17,728 --> 00:31:20,639
- Hold your position. I'll be right there.
- Copy.

279
00:31:30,443 --> 00:31:32,797
Hi, Jamey.

280
00:31:34,163 --> 00:31:36,437
What's this all about?

281
00:31:36,522 --> 00:31:39,718
- Why don't you tell us?
- I've no idea what you're talking about.

282
00:31:39,802 --> 00:31:43,555
- Who were you going to contact?
- None of your business. It was personal.

283
00:31:43,641 --> 00:31:46,073
The same people who set me up to be killed?

284
00:31:46,159 --> 00:31:49,912
- To be killed? What are you talking about?
- We don't have time for this.

285
00:31:49,998 --> 00:31:53,751
Talk to us, Jamey. Who's got
Jack's wife and daughter?

286
00:31:53,836 --> 00:31:56,750
- What are they making Jack do?
- I don't know!

287
00:31:57,317 --> 00:31:59,989
Richard Walsh is dead. So is Scott Baylor.

288
00:32:00,076 --> 00:32:05,194
You will be charged with murder and treason.
I suggest you tell me what's going on!

289
00:32:05,794 --> 00:32:09,069
- They told me nobody would get hurt.
- Who are "they"?

290
00:32:09,154 --> 00:32:12,827
- I can't tell you.
- Telling us everything is the only way out!

291
00:32:12,912 --> 00:32:14,903
You understand?

292
00:32:16,472 --> 00:32:21,146
I was just supposed to tap into the
surveillance. All the security cameras.

293
00:32:21,230 --> 00:32:23,823
Then they asked me
to start sending messages.

294
00:32:24,029 --> 00:32:26,020
What messages?

295
00:32:26,109 --> 00:32:28,099
What messages?!

296
00:32:30,949 --> 00:32:32,939
Mostly about Jack.

297
00:32:33,747 --> 00:32:39,775
Then about the key card. I didn't know this
was gonna happen. You have to believe that.

298
00:32:39,866 --> 00:32:43,334
OK, fine. We do. But now you have to help us.

299
00:32:43,425 --> 00:32:45,461
Who were you doing all this for?

300
00:32:47,503 --> 00:32:51,814
- No. I have to talk to someone first.
- What? No! There is no time, Jamey!

301
00:32:51,902 --> 00:32:57,692
Palmer is exposed. Jack's family is in danger.
You have to start talking to us. Now!

302
00:33:00,220 --> 00:33:04,974
All right, look, I'll make sure everything you
tell us goes into cutting you a deal, OK?

303
00:33:08,378 --> 00:33:12,164
No, I'm not saying anything.
Not until I get agency counsel.

304
00:33:35,571 --> 00:33:37,845
Sit.

305
00:33:37,930 --> 00:33:43,765
As Mayor of Los Angeles, I often get the
opportunity to meet truly remarkable people.

306
00:33:43,848 --> 00:33:48,319
People that strive for the greater good,
that work to make our world a better place.

307
00:33:48,408 --> 00:33:53,685
One of those people is here today, and
"remarkable" only begins to describe him.

308
00:33:53,766 --> 00:33:57,917
Ladies and gentlemen, the next president
of the United States, and my good friend,

309
00:33:58,005 --> 00:33:59,801
David Palmer.

310
00:34:21,518 --> 00:34:24,829
I love you, Kimberly. You know that?

311
00:34:26,037 --> 00:34:28,027
Yeah.

312
00:34:29,956 --> 00:34:31,948
Good.

313
00:34:32,994 --> 00:34:35,792
It's important that you know that.

314
00:34:37,315 --> 00:34:40,385
Mom, if you're feeling guilty
about our fight yesterday...

315
00:34:40,474 --> 00:34:42,862
I'm over it. I just wanna get home.

316
00:34:42,952 --> 00:34:47,468
That's not why I'm saying that.
It's just... we're stuck in this awful place

317
00:34:47,551 --> 00:34:50,542
and I just want you to know
that you're not alone.

318
00:34:53,870 --> 00:34:55,861
Mom, you're scaring me.

319
00:34:57,750 --> 00:35:01,297
It's like you're saying this cos you
know something bad's gonna happen.

320
00:35:01,388 --> 00:35:03,378
No, no, no, no.

321
00:35:05,706 --> 00:35:07,698
It's just...

322
00:35:09,786 --> 00:35:15,655
I'm trying to explain to you what a simple,
powerful thing my love for you is.

323
00:35:17,584 --> 00:35:22,656
So no matter how bad things get, or how
good they get, that's not gonna change.

324
00:35:26,062 --> 00:35:28,813
I just don't know how
to do anything but love you.

325
00:35:48,895 --> 00:35:51,853
Thank you. Thank you very much.

326
00:35:53,774 --> 00:35:55,332
Thank you.

327
00:35:55,733 --> 00:35:58,122
- I'll be right back.
- Thank you.

328
00:36:00,812 --> 00:36:03,121
Thank you, Mayor Nelson.

329
00:36:03,212 --> 00:36:06,646
And thank you, kind citizens of Los Angeles.

330
00:36:12,008 --> 00:36:13,806
Identification, please.

331
00:36:13,889 --> 00:36:18,836
Now, this country
depends on a healthy economy in California.

332
00:36:20,288 --> 00:36:23,517
And the nucleus of that economy is energy.

333
00:36:23,887 --> 00:36:25,319
Jack, step out.

334
00:36:25,686 --> 00:36:27,677
We're ready for you.

335
00:36:28,645 --> 00:36:32,431
- To do what?
- Relax, it will be over in five minutes.

336
00:36:33,802 --> 00:36:37,033
.. is standing
right here in this room today.

337
00:36:42,642 --> 00:36:45,473
Do you see the photographer?

338
00:36:46,441 --> 00:36:49,431
- Yeah, I see him.
- Go over and join him.

339
00:36:59,197 --> 00:37:02,871
After he shoots Palmer,
he will hand you his weapon.

340
00:37:02,956 --> 00:37:06,071
- You gotta be kidding me.
- I know you'll be tempted to intervene,

341
00:37:06,156 --> 00:37:11,353
but you must believe me, if you do, your
family dies and we'll get Palmer anyway.

342
00:37:13,553 --> 00:37:14,702
I understand.

343
00:37:14,832 --> 00:37:18,029
When I started my campaign over a year ago,

344
00:37:19,272 --> 00:37:21,944
I made a promise to you who supported me

345
00:37:22,592 --> 00:37:28,540
that my campaign would be built on
integrity, commitment, and above all, honour.

346
00:37:32,508 --> 00:37:34,498
Thank you.

347
00:37:36,667 --> 00:37:38,658
Thank you.

348
00:37:54,222 --> 00:37:56,452
Agent Bauer?

349
00:37:56,541 --> 00:37:59,261
Alan Hayes, Secret Service.
I need you to come with me.

350
00:37:59,501 --> 00:38:02,856
- What's the matter?
- No problem, just come with me.

351
00:38:08,139 --> 00:38:09,934
Seven years ago...

352
00:38:11,099 --> 00:38:13,054
Gun! Gun!

353
00:38:18,335 --> 00:38:20,930
- Get him out!
- Somebody get Sherry!

354
00:38:22,256 --> 00:38:25,132
- Looks like Palmer's being shielded.
- Yeah, but why?

355
00:38:25,334 --> 00:38:28,531
Bauer! Bauer, what's happening?
Bauer, did you screw me?!

356
00:38:29,333 --> 00:38:30,527
I didn't do this.

357
00:38:30,614 --> 00:38:33,844
Do you understand?
Please, don't hurt my family.

358
00:38:36,772 --> 00:38:39,410
Don't hurt my family! I'll help, I promise!

359
00:38:39,490 --> 00:38:43,482
- Please! Please!
- That's it, we're done. Kill the wife and kid.

360
00:38:49,088 --> 00:38:50,919
Get outta here!

361
00:39:08,922 --> 00:39:11,231
I don't have time for this.

362
00:39:21,319 --> 00:39:22,593
- Hello?
- What do you want?

363
00:39:22,679 --> 00:39:25,238
Division wanted to pick up
Bauer at the power plant.

364
00:39:25,518 --> 00:39:28,157
- They've been looking for him all night.
- Why?

365
00:39:28,237 --> 00:39:30,591
He's been breaking protocol
since you got to him.

366
00:39:30,678 --> 00:39:33,236
Dammit!

367
00:39:41,515 --> 00:39:43,982
No! Oh, God!

368
00:39:44,073 --> 00:39:46,632
No! No!

369
00:40:11,547 --> 00:40:13,536
Gimme your hand.

370
00:40:16,585 --> 00:40:18,780
Please don't!

371
00:40:21,023 --> 00:40:23,413
- Eli?
- Yeah?

372
00:40:24,342 --> 00:40:26,936
I still need 'em alive.

373
00:40:27,023 --> 00:40:29,297
Both of 'em?

374
00:40:40,258 --> 00:40:42,648
Yeah. Take 'em back.

375
00:40:42,649 --> 00:40:43,649
No...

